  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "6f936f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 0,
      "content": "GENERAL INFORMATION FOR ALL MINORS",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "90c86f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "UC Santa Cruz students may complete one or more minors, provided they can finish all required coursework within their maximum enrollment terms and credit limits. Minors are recorded on the official transcript but do not appear on the diploma. Pursuing a minor is optional and should align with a student’s academic interests and career goals. Students do not apply for minors as part of their UC Santa Cruz admission application. Transfer students interested in a minor should reach out to the department that offers it for advising during their first quarter of enrollment.",
      "contentHtml": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">UC Santa Cruz students may complete one or more minors, provided they can finish all required coursework within their maximum enrollment terms and credit limits. Minors are recorded on the official transcript but do not appear on the diploma. Pursuing a minor is optional and should align with a student’s academic interests and career goals.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Students do not apply for minors as part of their UC Santa Cruz admission application. Transfer students interested in a minor should reach out to the department that offers it for advising during their first quarter of enrollment.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "70936f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 2,
      "content": "SCIENCE, TECHNOLOGY, ENGINEERING, AND MATHEMATICS (STEM) EDUCATION MINOR",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "72936f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 3,
      "content": "The STEM Education Minor is designed to serve students in STEM majors who are considering careers in secondary mathematics or science teaching. This minor includes approximately 75 hours of classroom field placements. PREPARATION FOR THE MINOR Choose one of the following courses: EDUC 50A: CAL Teach 1: Science and Mathematics EDUC 50B: CAL Teach 1: Mathematics EDUC 50C: CAL Teach 1: Science Plus the following course: EDUC 60: Schooling, Democracy, and Justice Please visit the Education website to learn more about this minor. UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Science Technology Engineering and Mathematics (STEM) Education Minor Program Statement",
      "contentHtml": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The STEM Education Minor is designed to serve students in STEM majors who are considering careers in secondary mathematics or science teaching.&nbsp;This minor includes approximately 75 hours of classroom field placements.</span></p><p><br></p><h2><strong>PREPARATION FOR THE MINOR</strong></h2><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Choose one of the following courses:</strong></p><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">EDUC 50A: CAL Teach 1: Science and Mathematics</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">EDUC 50B: CAL Teach 1: Mathematics</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">EDUC 50C: CAL Teach 1: Science</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Plus the following course:</strong></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">EDUC 60: Schooling, Democracy, and Justice</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Please visit the </span><a href=\"https://education.ucsc.edu/academics/ba-program-minors/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Education website</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> to learn more about this minor.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://catalog.ucsc.edu/en/current/general-catalog/academic-units/social-sciences-division/education/science-technology-engineering-and-mathematics-stem-education-minor/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Science Technology Engineering and Mathematics (STEM) Education Minor Program Statement</a></p>"
    }
  ],
